{
  "local_port": 47856,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best recipes for small batch chocolate chip cookies?",
  "response": "Absolutely! Baking a small batch of chocolate chip cookies is perfect for satisfying your sweet tooth without making too many. Below are two delicious recipes tailored for small batches, along with some helpful tips and variations.\n\n---\n\n## **1. Classic Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies**\n\n### **Ingredients:**\n- **4 tablespoons (1/4 cup) unsalted butter**, softened\n- **1/4 cup granulated sugar**\n- **1/4 cup packed light brown sugar**\n- **1/2 large egg** (beat one egg and use half; alternatively, use 2 tablespoons of beaten egg)\n- **1 teaspoon vanilla extract**\n- **3/4 cup all-purpose flour**\n- **1/4 teaspoon baking soda**\n- **1/4 teaspoon salt**\n- **1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips**\n\n### **Instructions:**\n\n1. **Preheat the Oven:**\n   - Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C).\n   - Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.\n\n2. **Mix the Butter and Sugars:**\n   - In a medium mixing bowl, cream together the softened butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar until smooth and creamy.\n\n3. **Add Egg and Vanilla:**\n   - Beat in the half egg (or the equivalent 2 tablespoons) and vanilla extract until well combined.\n\n4. **Combine Dry Ingredients:**\n   - In a separate bowl, whisk together the all-purpose flour, baking soda, and salt.\n\n5. **Mix Wet and Dry Ingredients:**\n   - Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture, stirring until just combined.\n\n6. **Fold in Chocolate Chips:**\n   - Gently fold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed.\n\n7. **Scoop the Dough:**\n   - Use a tablespoon or a small ice cream scoop to portion out the dough onto the prepared baking sheet. Space them about 2 inches apart to allow for spreading.\n\n8. **Bake:**\n   - Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the edges are golden brown but the centers are still soft.\n\n9. **Cool:**\n   - Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for about 5 minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n### **Yield:**\nApproximately 12-15 cookies\n\n---\n\n## **2. Chewy Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies**\n\n### **Ingredients:**\n- **5 tablespoons (about 1/3 cup) unsalted butter**, melted\n- **1/4 cup packed brown sugar**\n- **2 tablespoons granulated sugar**\n- **1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract**\n- **1 egg yolk** (discard or save the white for another use)\n- **3/4 cup all-purpose flour**\n- **1/4 teaspoon baking soda**\n- **1/4 teaspoon salt**\n- **1/2 cup chocolate chips** (milk, dark, or a mix)\n\n### **Instructions:**\n\n1. **Preheat the Oven:**\n   - Preheat your oven to 325\u00b0F (165\u00b0C).\n   - Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\n\n2. **Combine Wet Ingredients:**\n   - In a mixing bowl, whisk together the melted butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n   - Beat in the egg yolk until fully incorporated.\n\n3. **Add Dry Ingredients:**\n   - In a separate bowl, mix the all-purpose flour, baking soda, and salt.\n   - Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture, stirring until just combined.\n\n4. **Incorporate Chocolate Chips:**\n   - Fold in the chocolate chips evenly.\n\n5. **Portion the Dough:**\n   - Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\n\n6. **Bake:**\n   - Bake for 10-12 minutes, or until the edges are set and slightly golden. The centers may look undercooked but will firm up as they cool.\n\n7. **Cool:**\n   - Let the cookies cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n### **Yield:**\nApproximately 12 cookies\n\n---\n\n## **Tips for Perfect Small Batch Cookies:**\n\n1. **Accurate Measuring:**\n   - For small batches, precise measuring is crucial. Consider using kitchen scales for better accuracy, especially with flour.\n\n2. **Softened Butter:**\n   - Ensure the butter is properly softened (room temperature) for better creaming with sugars, which affects the texture.\n\n3. **Chilling the Dough (Optional):**\n   - Refrigerate the dough for 15-30 minutes before baking to prevent excessive spreading and enhance flavor.\n\n4. **Baking Time:**\n   - Keep a close eye on the cookies as small batches can bake quickly. Start checking a minute before the suggested baking time.\n\n5. **Storage:**\n   - Store cookies in an airtight container at room temperature for up to a week. You can also freeze the dough balls on a baking sheet, then transfer to a freezer bag for future baking.\n\n## **Variations:**\n\n- **Add Nuts:** Incorporate 1/4 cup of chopped walnuts or pecans for added crunch.\n- **Different Chips:** Swap chocolate chips for white chocolate, dark chocolate chunks, or even peanut butter chips.\n- **Sea Salt Sprinkle:** Before baking, lightly sprinkle a tiny bit of sea salt on top of each cookie for a sweet-salty flavor contrast.\n\nEnjoy baking your delicious small batch chocolate chip cookies!",
